So I finally have a day off from work... the nice thing about not actually being put on the schedule(I never could spell that word, yay spell check) is that I can take off on occasion when I want to.  And damn did I need a day off.  So as the world turns and new things unfold my life remains surprisingly the same.  Little new dramas, dilemmas, and experiences make impacts here and there; but it's nothing out of the ordinary.  What I wouldn't give for something out of the ordinary right now...

I went to a Open Meeting for my business on tuesday night, and I hadn't realized how much I missed it.  I'll be back to going every tuesday now for sure.  I always leave them totally psyched and ready to change the world (so to speak).  The people there are wonderful and the speaker has a great presence that is guaranteed to make you laugh.  It reminds me that being optimistic is a good thing; and helps me to get closer to my goals.  The Team Meeting in Virgina was fun, except for the rain and the getting lost part; but it was worth it.  I got to see some of the true leaders on my team and hear all sorts of interesting updates.  I can't wait to be among them.  I look at some of these people and hear their stories from before they got involved with our business and to me it is almost miraculous how much they have changed.  If there is one thing I can say about it all... it is that this Team will change your life, and most definitely for the better.

on another random misadventure.  This time to Richmond Virgina.  *sighs*  I really hope I can find a place to crash on my way home because I don't know if I can drive from mindnight to 6am by myself.  Time to make phone calls.  Okay kiddies... gotta go.  *laughs*  How do I get myself into these things.  I sware, I like driving I really do.

If there is an devil on your friends list you would like to take, cuddle tenderly, gradually undress, lick them until they scream, then make love to them until both of you are glowing and totally fulfilled, then snuggle for about an hour and do it all over again, then post this exact sentence in YOUR journal.


So, I accidently took a 3 hour nap and now it is 10'oclock and I am just getting online; but at least I feel refreshed.

Okay sooooo.... *blinks and rereads the little quiz thing* This is marginally disturbing and still rather acurate. *shrugs* But hey, what can I say... I have always had a summer home on Styxx... maybe in Styxx *giggles* Nah, I like Acheron better. *winks to any and all who get the referance*

So I'm sick again, somehow it just doesn't supprise me anymore.  I've gotten Strep Throat for the millionth (exadurated) time this year.  I have an appointment to go see a Specailist ENT Dr. on Friday, hopefully they will aggree to just take my tonsils out.  I would love them very much if they did.  I am just tired of being sick... it feels like my life is measured by going from one illness to another, and it sucks.  I have stuff that I need to do, stuff that I warent as important, and having a feaver as well as having trouble breathing, definalty puts a kink in my plans.
Well anyway, if I do end up going in for surgery I will be "out of it" for at least 2 and a half weeks according to my Dr. and when I take that into concideration I realize I will probobly just take a few weeks off school.  That means I will need to retake EL2, but that isn't such a bad thing.  It's funny though, most people have to reatake classes because their grade were bad... I have a 94.5%, but as of now I also have 25 hours to make up... and building.  I think that maybe it will do me some good to concentrait on getting healthy for a while.  
Anyhow, I hope I am doing okay with this online journal thing... I guess I am trying.  There's just nothing I really want to rant about.  *smiles and shrugs*  Maybe I'm just too tired to rant.

So congratulations people... you have finally convinced me to start writing in here.  So what can I say??  Well I think I should start with the fact that I don't believe in "online diary's."  So if you are reading this in the hopes of getting "cool" blackmail information, don't bother.  I don't understand the concept of exposing your personal life on the computer.  I mean sure, I understand the idea that it is supposed to be a journal, therefor it is supposed to be private... but come on people... it's the internet.  And NOTHING is private on the internet.  So I don't think people have the right to complain when others find out their personal information because they chose to post it online.  So in short, sure I'll write in here... but it wont be anything that anyone will be able to use against me.  *shrugs*  Sorry if that disappoints anyone.
